<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/460</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-18"><hi rend="italic">February 18,
                                    1921</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received February 26.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 753</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that I have
                            brought the Department’s telegram of February the 11th to the attention
                            of President Menocal, who assures me that no effort will be made to pass
                            the <pb facs="0822" n="698" xml:id="pg_698"/> new budget requiring about
                            $104,000,000 to run the Cuban Government, but that it will function for
                            the coming fiscal year under the 1918–1919 budget.</p>
                        <p>More detailed information regarding the proposed new budget is to be
                            furnished me in the near future.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Boaz W. Long</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>